parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the power steering to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the power steering assist fails to operate
the steering wheel becomes heavy or stiff
the vehicle is difficult to steer
and the EPS indicator light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a potential fault in the airbag system, which can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the instrument panel illuminates
indicating a problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag inflator recall can cause the airbag to rupture or not deploy properly in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the instrument panel illuminates
indicating a problem with the airbag system; the airbag may not deploy properly in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of repair parts can cause inconvenience to the vehicle owner and potentially lead to accidents or injuries due to the faulty airbag system.
symptoms: The vehicle owner is unable to obtain the necessary repair parts to fix the airbag system
leading to a delay in the repair process.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks into the vehicle, causing damage to the electrical system, mold growth, and health hazards.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the spare tire compartment
rear seat wells
and floor mats; mold growth on carpeting and seats; musty smell; foggy windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to unlock the door, potentially leaving the driver stranded or in an emergency situation.
symptoms: Key fails to unlock the driver's side door; lock cylinder needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The low beam headlights fail to work
the high beam headlights fail to work
the headlights flicker on and off
the headlights suddenly go out
the headlights do not return to their normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The wiring harness fails
the headlight switch fails
the fuse blows
the electrical system shorts out.
